posts.name: 55 South
posts.note: 55 South is an industrial space for inventive Southern comfort eats along with specialty drinks and weekend brunch. You need to order the hot chicken sandwich or the jambalaya. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Asia Kitchen
posts.note: Asia Kitchen serves freshly prepared Chinese food. There is nothing fancy about the interior, and it is the food that you come for. Asia Kitchen isn’t for everybody; but if you crave an authentic experience, you need to visit. The full menu, available all day is offered in both Chinese (Mandarin?) and English. The menu presents a slate of unfamiliar dishes: Shredded Pork in Garlic Sauce, Beef with Sour Vegetable, etc.

posts.name: Bellevue Diner
posts.note: The Bellevue Diner is an authentic Greek and Mediterranean diner with an emphasis on locally-sourced ingredients from Nashville. They serve up home-cooked, affordable meals in an American diner setting. People have been known to fall in love with their gyros, burgers, Greek omelettes, pasta dishes, eggs Benedict, and wraps.

posts.name: Betty's Grill
posts.note: Betty's Grill is a mellow, cash-only and smoker-friendly neighborhood haunt with pub grub, live bands, pool, and beer.

posts.name: Bolton’s Spicy Chicken and Fish
posts.note: Bolton’s Spicy Chicken and Fish is a local fast-food chain serving spicy chicken, plus ribs, fish, and Southern sides, in a no-frills space. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Bryant's Breakfast
posts.note: Bryant's Breakfast is a bustling, counter-serve eatery dishing out classic Southern breakfast and lunch fare. Unless you get to Bryant's Breakfast when they open, plan on having to wait in line for an hour or more. I ordered two breakfast sandwiches, and my favorite was the Bologna with egg and cheese on a biscuit.

posts.name: Charlie Vergos' Rendezvous
posts.note: Charlie Vergos' Rendezvous is a BBQ spot with upstairs beer hall serving up racks of smoked ribs and sausages dusted with dry rub. Need to order the lamb riblets, which is their sleeper dish. I still think about the lamb riblets when I talk about BBQ to people or Memphis.

posts.name: Dandgure's Classic Southern Cooking
posts.note: Dandgure's Classic Southern Cooking is a long-standing cafeteria-style establishment providing Southern lunch staples in down-home surrounds.

posts.name: Dino's Bar
posts.note: Dino's Bar is an old-school operation serving up straightforward burgers, fries, and beer in an easygoing setting. From their website, 'As East Nashville’s oldest dive bar, Dino’s stays true to its roots. Serving classic burgers and fries, Dino’s is a neighborhood watering hole for locals and visitors alike. Dino’s is fine food and cold beer. Known across the country for the “Dino’s cheeseburger”.'

posts.name: Dyer's Burgers
posts.note: Dyer's Burgers is a popular diner known for using the same grease to deep-fry their burgers and fries for over a century.

posts.name: Farm House Restaurant
posts.note: Farm House Restaurant serves an all you can eat buffet available every day and catfish buffet on Friday and Saturday. You need to order the Biscuits with chocolate gravy. They even serve frogs legs from the photos I've seen.

posts.name: Fox's Donut Den
posts.note: Fox's Donut Den is an old-fashioned institution turning out classic donuts and pastries since 1973, plus they have bagels and coffee.

posts.name: The Grilled Cheeserie
posts.note: The Grilled Cheeserie is a popular food truck is serving up artisanal grilled cheese sandwiches and seasonal bites at the counter. You need to order the pimento cheese grilled mac and cheese.

posts.name: Gus's World Famous Fried Chicken
posts.note: Gus's World Famous Fried Chicken is a long-running chain serving spicy fried chicken and comfort sides in a low-key setting. From their website, 'Over 60 years ago in the small community of Mason, Tennessee, Napoleon “Na&rdquo Vanderbilt created something amazing – fried chicken that could unite a community. In an era of divisive racial attitudes, the residents of Mason found that they could all – black and white – agree on how much they loved Na’s fried chicken.'

posts.name: Hathorne
posts.note: From the Hathorne website, 'Chef John Stephenson’s culinary viewpoint is ‘new American;’ the ingredients and recipes he’s put together are inspired by his surroundings in the South, yet influenced by the ethnic threads that are woven into American culture, as well as John’s travels. Our menu features familiar ingredients and cooking methods, but they’re presented in special and unexpected ways featuring big flavors full of vibrant colors that celebrate the best of the season.'

posts.name: Hattie B's Hot Chicken
posts.note: Hattie B‘s Hot Chicken serves mild to very spicy fried chicken, Southern sides, and local brews in a casual, counter-service eatery.

posts.name: Hog and Hominy
posts.note: Hog and Hominy is a lively restaurant and bar serving Southern-influenced Italian dishes along with creative cocktails.

posts.name: King Market
posts.note: King Market is a market featuring Asian groceries and a casual Thai-Laotian cafe serving Pho, Pad Thai, Loa food, curries, and beer.

posts.name: Leonard's Pit Barbecue
posts.note: Leonard's Pit Barbecue is a no-frills, venerable barbecue spot dispensing slow-cooked pork, and ribs, along with lunch and dinner buffets. You need to order the chopped pork sandwich, sweet mustard coleslaw, onion ring batter, and pulled pork. From the Food Network website, 'Leonard's Pit Barbecue owner Dan Brown says if you visit for dinner you'll experience the same delicious recipes passed down from “last century” to “last week”. Open since 1922, this iconic Memphis, TN, eatery has loads of fans, who call the chopped pork sandwich “all-star barbecue”.'

posts.name: Lunchbox Eats
posts.note: Lunchbox Eats is a laid-back eatery serving sandwiches, comfort food, and desserts in a casual space with patio seating. Order the graduation meatloaf sandwich or turkey sandwich with home made slaw.

posts.name: Martin’s Bar-B-Que Joint
posts.note: Martin’s Bar-B-Que Joint has a pit for cooking whole pigs which dominates the homey dining room at this popular BBQ emporium. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Mas Tacos Por Favor
posts.note: Mas Tacos Por Favor is a snug, no-frills Mexican restaurant fixing up an array of tacos and other standards. You need to order the chicken tamale which is only served on Wednesday's and during the holidays or Pozole Verde Soup or the sweet potato and quinoa tacos.

posts.name: Miss Girlee Soul Food Restaurant
posts.note: Miss Girlee Soul Food Restaurant is a no-nonsense counter-serve joint serving down-home fare like fried chicken, meatloaf, and catfish.

posts.name: Payne's Bar-B-Que
posts.note: Payne's Bar-B-Que is a simple cinder block building serving acclaimed chopped and pulled pork sandwiches along with smoked sausage too.

posts.name: Peg Leg Porker BBQ
posts.note: Peg Leg Porker BBQ serves pulled pork, ribs, fried pies, and buckets of beer on the patio or in the plain but soulful interior.

posts.name: Prince's Hot Chicken Shack
posts.note: Prince's Hot Chicken Shack is known for Nashville's unique deep-fried poultry specialty, spiced from mild to ultra hot levels. I went with medium spicy because I figured I could go hotter next time instead of burning my mouth off.

posts.name: Richy Kreme Do-Nuts
posts.note: From the Richy Kreme Do-Nuts website, 'In 1939 Marion Richardson moved to Blount County with his family. Prior to that, he and his brother were operating a doughnut franchise in Virginia. Saying he had a flour blend that would make a better doughnut, Mr. Richardson went back into the business. In 1948, Marion Richardson began serving doughnuts at a shop on Old Knoxville Highway across from Eagleton Ball Park. Richy Kreme Do-Nuts has become a Blount County tradition ever since.' When you are there, you need to eat one of their apple fritters along with a white cream-filled donut.

posts.name: Rotier's Restaurant
posts.note: Rotier's Restaurant is an old-fashioned bar and grill known for cheeseburgers on French bread and thick milkshakes. It’s a meat and three places that serve great burgers too.

posts.name: Silver Sands Café
posts.note: Silver Sands Café is a family owned restaurant that serves some of the best homemade southern style food in the Downtown Nashville area. Popular family recipes have been passed down three generations now, including smothered pork chops, potatoes, and onions, salmon croquettes, fried chicken, mac and cheese, greens, hot water cornbread, and so much more.

posts.name: Tailor Nashville
posts.note: From the Tailor Nashville website, 'Tailor Nashville offers a simple, timeless dining experience that emulates an intimate dinner party in the way it fills both the bodies and souls of its guests. Culinary Creator Vivek Surti honors his heritage through the South Asian American cuisine that is representative of Surti being a first-generation American of Indian descent. At Tailor Nashville, guests are welcomed and enjoy eight to ten dishes that are explained by the chefs with high touch service.'

posts.name: Vienna Coffee House
posts.note: From the Vienna Coffee House website, 'The Vienna Coffee House opened the doors on October 6th, 2010, with a goal to be THE great neighborhood coffeehouse in Maryville, TN. We serve premier espresso drinks, (Mocha, Latte, traditional Cappuccino) crafted by serious Baristas and freshly roasted specialty coffees from the Vienna Coffee Company Roastery, located in the lower level of the coffee house. We strive to DELIGHT the customer with every visit! In addition to great coffee, we serve up a variety of teas, chai, smoothies, steamers, and lots of fresh baked goods made in house, and other delicious food items.' They have live music from 6:00 PM - 7:30 PM on Friday nights, but make sure to check the schedule.
